titlestmt.titleproper: A Guide to the Ford Foundation records, General Correspondence FA735

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2015-08-11 19:04:32 -0400.

did.physdesc: The Ford Foundation’s General Correspondence files for the years 1951-1970 are housed on 669 reels of microfilm and number sequentially from C-1138 to C-1806, including two ‘A’ numbered reels. General Correspondence Files for 1951 - 1960 are housed on 280 reels of 35mm microfilm, and numbered C-1138 thru C-1416 (including two ‘A’ numbered reels), while the files for 1961 - 1970 are housed on 389 reels of 16mm microfilm, and numbered C-1417 thru C-1806.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for scholarly research.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: Ford Foundation General Correspondence Files for 1951-1964 are arranged by year, then alphabetically by file heading.
General Correspondence Files for the years 1965-1970 are arranged by year, then by the Foundation's Division/Program, and alphabetically by file heading within the Division/Program.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

phystech.head: Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements
phystech.p: Materials requiring specialized equipment for access (film, audio, video, slides) may be restricted from scholarly research dependent on availability of the applicable equipment.
Brittle or damaged items, or materials otherwise in need of preservation care, may be restricted from scholarly research at the discretion of the RAC Head of Archival Services/RAC Head of Reference.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Completion of a use agreement is required prior to providing scholarly access. See RAC Head of Reference (or applicable designee) for details.
Ford Foundation holds title, copyright and literary rights in the collection, in so far as it holds them.

The Rockefeller Archive Center has authority to grant permission to cite and publish material from the collection for scholarly purposes. Permission to publish extensive excerpts, or material in its entirety, will be referred to the Ford Foundation.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Ford Foundation archive was deposited at RAC in 2011. Ford Foundation records, correspondence, reports, program files and officers papers were transferred to, and accessioned by, RAC beginning in 2011. Accessions continue as necessary.

otherfindaid.head: Other Finding Aids note
otherfindaid.p: General Correspondence Files for 1951-1970 are indexed by the Ford Foundation’s Central Index cards, 1950-1975 (FA736). However, the index cards are no longer an accurate index of the General Correspondence files on microfilm, as these files were "weeded" prior to microfilming. It appears the index cards were not updated to reflect the destroyed correspondence.

The Central Index cards do provide indexing for correspondence after 1970, but these files are not housed in the General Correspondence Files. Correspondence indexed as “Gen 71…” or later might be found in the departmental Program/Division collections of correspondence, which are including in the individual ‘Office Files’ collections.
